column6: Black Powder Coated Goldtone Metal Watch Tips 12k Pink and Green Gold Leaves Goldtone Expansion Band According to legend, a French goldsmith named Henri LeBeau became lost during the "gold rush days" of the middle 1870's in the Black Hills of South Dakota and fell asleep believing he was dying of thirst and starvation. During a dream, he saw a mountain stream with grapevines growing on its banks. Upon awakening, he walked over a rise and found the stream and grapevines just as he had in his dream and, out of gratitude, dedicated his life and talents to creating jewelry in the shapes of grape clusters and leaves fashioned in pink, green and yellow gold. Today, a series of up to 40 different steps are necessary to capture the same dramatic detail in our traditional and contemporary Black Hills Gold designs.

column6: Sterling Silver Watch Tips 12k Pink and Green Gold Leaves Stainless Steel Expansion Band According to legend, a French goldsmith named Henri LeBeau became lost during the "gold rush days" of the middle 1870's in the Black Hills of South Dakota and fell asleep believing he was dying of thirst and starvation. During a dream, he saw a mountain stream with grapevines growing on its banks. Upon awakening, he walked over a rise and found the stream and grapevines just as he had in his dream and, out of gratitude, dedicated his life and talents to creating jewelry in the shapes of grape clusters and leaves fashioned in pink, green and yellow gold. Today, a series of up to 40 different steps are necessary to capture the same dramatic detail in our traditional and contemporary Black Hills Gold designs.

The altimeter and barometer as well as the compass and thermometer can all be activated with one touch, making the watch as easy to use as it is to wear. column6: Sterling Silver Watch Tips 12k Pink and Green Gold Leaves Stainless Steel Expansion Band According to legend, a French goldsmith named Henri LeBeau became lost during the "gold rush days" of the middle 1870's in the Black Hills of South Dakota and fell asleep believing he was dying of thirst and starvation. During a dream, he saw a mountain stream with grapevines growing on its banks. Upon awakening, he walked over a rise and found the stream and grapevines just as he had in his dream and, out of gratitude, dedicated his life and talents to creating jewelry in the shapes of grape clusters and leaves fashioned in pink, green and yellow gold. Today, a series of up to 40 different steps are necessary to capture the same dramatic detail in our traditional and contemporary Black Hills Gold designs.

column6: Sterling Silver Watch Tips 12k Pink and Green Gold Leaves Genuine Onyx Stainless Steel Expansion Band According to legend, a French goldsmith named Henri LeBeau became lost during the "gold rush days"of the middle 1870's in the Black Hills of South Dakota and fell asleep believing he was dying of thirst and starvation. During a dream, he saw a mountain stream with grapevines growing on its banks. Upon awakening, he walked over a rise and found the stream and grapevines just as he had in his dream and, out of gratitude, dedicated his life and talents to creating jewelry in the shapes of grape clusters and leaves fashioned in pink, green and yellow gold. Today, a series of up to 40 different steps are necessary to capture the same dramatic detail in our traditional and contemporary Black Hills Gold designs. Most colored gemstones are treated to enhance their natural appearance. Some treatments are not permanent and may require special care. See Buying Guide for details.

column1: Ladies' Eco-Drive Stainless Steel Ciena
column5: Ladies' Eco-Drive Ciena Watch: No Batteries Required The Citizen Ladies' Eco-Drive Stainless Steel Ciena Watch offers you the latest timekeeping technology in this watch that never needs a battery. The Eco-Drive Watch converts natural and artificial light to energy that it then stores in a rechargeable Lithium-ion battery so there is no old-fashioned winding and no battery replacement needed. This is the watch you have always wanted - the timeless one that keeps time forever. The Citizen Ladies' Eco-Drive Ciena Watch is designed in classically beautiful long-wearing stainless steel and features a white dial with roman numerals and blue hour, minute and second hands. The watch is adorned with a 20-diamond bezel holding the spherical glass securely in place. Built by Citizen whose timekeeping tradition brings you quality, precision and style.
column6: The Citizen Ladies' Eco-Drive Stainless Steel Ciena Watch brings you the watch you have imagined - no winding, no new batteries - just a watch that keeps time running continuously The Eco-Drive watch takes in the light around it whatever the source and transforms that light into power which it stores in the Lithium-ion battery The watch is not only eco-friendly but good-looking with sophisticated stainless steel, a white dial with blue accents and roman numerals and a dazzling diamond bezel Citizen Limited Warranty Sears Satisfaction Guarantee

column1: Men's Eco-Drive Perpetual Chrono Watch
column5: Keep Time Well with the Citizen Men's Eco-Drive Atomic Timekeeping Watch When time is of the essence, turn to this men's Eco-Drive perpetual chrono watch by Citizen, featuring innovative Eco-Drive technology that enables a permanently rechargeable lithium-ion cell to recharge solely by using the power of light from any source, whether natural or artificial, direct or ambient. As the light passes through the dial to a solar panel it converts to renewable energy. No battery is ever required. For the man who needs superior accuracy, the Citizen men's Eco-Drive atomic Timekeeping watch is actually synchronized to the atomic clock through an internal receiver that captures signals from a generating tower and displays the precise time all the time.
